    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-21T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="193"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20 Mission/2–2148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-21T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 21, 1948—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—3:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. Wei Li-huang<note n="40" xml:id="d193fn40">Acting Director of Generalissimo
                        Chiang Kai-shek’s Northeast Headquarters (PNEH) and Commander-in-Chief of
                        Northeast Bandit Suppression Headquarters (NEBSH).</note> requested me make
                    inquiry re availability “two or three” American military advisors assist him
                    training northeastern troops (Contel 121 to Embassy, 89 to Dept. February
                        20).<note n="41" xml:id="d193fn41">
                        <ref target="frus1948v07#pg_103">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>, p.
                            103</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Embassy as 125, repeated Dept as 91.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
